We receive, collect and store any information you enter on our website or provide us in any other way. In addition, we collect the Internet protocol (IP) address used to connect your computer to the Internet; login; e-mail address; password; computer and connection information. We may use software tools to measure and collect session information, including page response times, length of visits to certain pages, page interaction information, and methods used to browse away from the page. We also collect personally identifiable information (including email, password, channel links);
How pulsoid collects information
When you create an account on our website, as part of the process, we collect personal information you give us such as your email address,password and channel link. When you use mobile application with heart rate monitor and Internet connection, we collect and store data received from mobile application, it includes: heart rate data(beats per minute) and timestamp. When you add and configure new widget, we save and collect widget configuration.
                            Pulsoid's signup and login services are completed through a secure server (HTTPS/SSL).
