                            To create and fill in User’s Space, which includes but not limited to Dashboard, Configuration section and Analytics for users, which includes only their own data received from website, mobile application.
How Pulsoid stores, uses, shares and discloses visitors' personal information
Your personal data is stored through separate databases on secure servers behind a firewall. The data with your heart rate is saved in secure way and is not connected to personal data directly and can not be associated with any user. Login data is stored as a hash digest and can’t be recovered by anyone. Heart rate data or login data won’t be transmitted to the 3rd party services. Your channel link might be shared but won’t be associated with your personal data. As soon as your heart rate is shown on stream, it can not be considered as personal data and can be associated with your channel.
